<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 2:56PM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Hot Conditions the Rest of this Afternoon...
Temperatures topping out in the lower to middle 90s combined
with dew points in the 70s, will lead to a period of heat index
readings around 100 through late afternoon.
Be sure to take precautions if you will be working or spending
time outside. Stay hydrated with plenty of non-alcoholic fluids.
And, if you will be outdoors be sure to take frequent breaks in
air-conditioned facilities.</description>
